<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 26 at 3:16PM EDT until April 26 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 PM EDT
FOR SOUTHERN ANSON AND RICHMOND COUNTIES...
At 315 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Rockingham, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Wadesboro, Hamlet, Hoffman, Ellerbe, Dobbins Heights,
Lilesville, Morven, Norman and McFarlan.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
